# Hosted MCP — when to use each tool

Exhaustive index: **every** tool on the hosted host with a one-line “when”. For **how to chain** tools, session rules, mount paths, and workflows, read **`hosted-mcp-orchestration.mdc` first**.

Prefer the matching **Cursor MCP server** (one URL path per server); do not reuse `Mcp-Session-Id` across paths.

**Always-on companion rules:** `hosted-mcp-orchestration.mdc` (playbook), `hosted-mcp-overview.mdc` (wiring, secrets, limits), `hosted-mcp-chia-knowledge.mdc`, `hosted-mcp-prompt-queue.mdc`, `hosted-mcp-agent-workspace.mdc`, `hosted-mcp-cron.mdc`, `hosted-mcp-context-persistence.mdc`. Optional skill: `.cursor/skills/hosted-mcp-routing/SKILL.md`.

Deeper context (slugs, triggers, how-to): `.cursor/rules/mcp-tools/<tool-with-hyphens>.mdc`. Regenerate this file and those rules together: `node tools/generate-mcp-tool-cursor-rules.mjs`.

## Conventions

- **`chia_knowledge_*`**: no `project` argument.
- **All other tools**: same stable **`project`** id on every call (alphanumeric start; then letters, digits, `.`, `_`, `-`).
- **Protocol documentation** → Chia graph tools. **Current chain / mempool / coins** → `coinset_*`.
- **`chia_knowledge_add_nugget`** / **`chia_knowledge_rebuild_reindex`**: curated corpus + indexer; treat as **dev/ops** unless the host is known writable.

## Quick routing

| Goal | Cursor server | Tools (examples) |
|------|---------------|------------------|
| Ground Chia facts from docs | `chia-knowledge` | `chia_knowledge_graph_rag_retrieve`, `chia_knowledge_blended_knowledge_lookup` |
| Live blockchain query | `coinset` | `coinset_post`, `coinset_operations` |
| FIFO deferred prompts | `prompt-queue` | `prompt_queue_enqueue`, `prompt_queue_pop`, … |
| Task DAG | `planner` | `planner_task_create`, `planner_task_next_ready`, … |
| Run / audit log | `ledger` | `ledger_run_start`, `ledger_run_append_event`, … |
| Working notes | `scratch` | `scratch_put`, `scratch_list`, … |
| Requirements | `spec` | `spec_define`, `spec_set_status`, … |
| HTTP check record | `verify` | `verify_run`, `verify_list`, … |
| Cron tick bundle | `cron` | `cron_tick_snapshot`, `cron_iteration_checkpoint` |
| After context flush | `session` | `session_restore`, `session_sanity_check` |

## `chia-knowledge` — `/mcp/chia`

- **`chia_knowledge_graph_rag_retrieve`** — You need authoritative Chia protocol / CLVM / wallet / farming documentation context from the knowledge graph, or raw RAG chunks to ground an answer.
- **`chia_knowledge_blended_knowledge_lookup`** — You want a single synthesized article-style answer (overview → prerequisites → core → related), not a flat list of nugget blocks.
- **`chia_knowledge_get_rag_subgraph`** — You already have specific nugget `semantic_ids` and want related graph context around those seeds.
- **`chia_knowledge_get_rag_learning_context`** — You want a prerequisite-ordered learning path / curriculum for a topic name.
- **`chia_knowledge_add_nugget`** — You are intentionally extending the curated nugget corpus (dev / editorial workflows), not normal Q&A.
- **`chia_knowledge_rebuild_reindex`** — Nuggets on disk changed or after `add_nugget`; dev/ops only on hosts with indexer tooling.

## `coinset` — `/mcp/coinset`

- **`coinset_operations`** — You need the catalog of Coinset HTTP operations as markdown (discovery), not a live chain call yet.
- **`coinset_post`** — You need live mainnet/testnet chain state (blocks, coins, mempool, etc.) via Coinset’s documented POST operations.

## `prompt-queue` — `/mcp/queue`

- **`prompt_queue_enqueue`** — Defer work to a later agent turn, human, or worker; FIFO per `project`.
- **`prompt_queue_pop`** — You are the consumer for that queue and should remove the oldest item.
- **`prompt_queue_peek`** — Inspect oldest queued prompt without consuming it.
- **`prompt_queue_queue_status`** — Check depth and oldest message id for a project namespace.

## `planner` — `/mcp/planner`

- **`planner_task_create`** — Add a node to the task DAG (title required).
- **`planner_task_update`** — Patch task fields after progress or scope change.
- **`planner_task_link`** — Task B must finish before task A can be treated as ready (dependency edge).
- **`planner_task_next_ready`** — Pick work: list tasks not done/cancelled whose dependencies are all done.
- **`planner_task_get`** — Fetch one task row and its outgoing dependency ids.
- **`planner_task_list`** — List/filter tasks (status, parent, limit).
- **`planner_export_json`** — Snapshot the project task graph for backup or migration.
- **`planner_import_json`** — Restore or merge a previously exported task graph for this project.

## `ledger` — `/mcp/ledger`

- **`ledger_run_start`** — Begin an episodic run (feature, cron tick, deploy) you will append events to.
- **`ledger_run_append_event`** — Log a milestone inside an open run.
- **`ledger_run_search`** — Full-text search across ledger event summaries/details.
- **`ledger_run_get_summary`** — Inspect run header and last N events.
- **`ledger_run_list`** — List runs for the project (open/closed filters as supported by schema).
- **`ledger_run_checkpoint`** — Append a compact checkpoint event and optionally refresh run summary / close run in one call.
- **`ledger_run_close`** — Finalize a run with optional closing summary.

## `scratch` — `/mcp/scratch`

- **`scratch_put`** — Store short-lived working notes, findings, or draft text keyed or tagged for this project.
- **`scratch_get`** — Fetch one scratch row by `id` or `key` (exactly one).
- **`scratch_list`** — Enumerate scratch entries with optional tag/pin/limit filters.
- **`scratch_pin`** — Pin important scratch rows so they surface in focus/session flows.
- **`scratch_unpin`** — Remove pin from a scratch row.
- **`scratch_delete`** — Remove a scratch entry explicitly.
- **`scratch_compact`** — Archive many scratch ids into one canonical body under a new key (cleanup before handoff).

## `evict` — `/mcp/evict`

- **`evict_suggest`** — Find scratch ids eligible for archive/delete (TTL, superseded, stale).
- **`evict_archive`** — Move selected scratch rows to cold storage; optionally remove from scratch.
- **`evict_delete`** — Hard-delete scratch rows when policy allows.
- **`evict_supersede_register`** — Mark older scratch rows superseded by a newer id for GC heuristics.

## `artifact` — `/mcp/artifact`

- **`artifact_register`** — Register a build output path or URI with optional task linkage and content hash.
- **`artifact_query`** — List artifacts with filters (task, path prefix, validity).
- **`artifact_invalidate`** — Soft-invalidate a stale artifact record.

## `constraint` — `/mcp/constraint`

- **`constraint_add`** — Record an invariant the implementation must respect.
- **`constraint_list`** — List active constraints for the project.
- **`constraint_revoke`** — Retire a constraint that no longer applies.

## `handoff` — `/mcp/handoff`

- **`handoff_build`** — Assemble a token-bounded markdown handoff from planner, ledger, scratch, artifacts, constraints.
- **`handoff_validate`** — Quick sanity counts (open runs, pending tasks, invalid artifacts) before shipping a handoff.
- **`handoff_save`** — Persist a markdown snapshot for `handoff_list` / `handoff_get` / `session_restore`.
- **`handoff_list`** — List saved handoff snapshots newest first.
- **`handoff_get`** — Fetch full body for one saved handoff id.

## `deploy` — `/mcp/deploy`

- **`deploy_record`** — Record a deployment (environment, version, notes) for audit trail.
- **`deploy_list`** — List deployment records for the project.
- **`deploy_get`** — Fetch one deployment row by id.
- **`deploy_latest`** — Get latest deployment for an environment.
- **`deploy_update`** — Patch an existing deployment record.
- **`deploy_search`** — Search deployment history text/metadata.

## `spec` — `/mcp/spec`

- **`spec_define`** — Create a requirement / acceptance criterion row.
- **`spec_update`** — Patch spec text, status metadata, or links.
- **`spec_get`** — Fetch one spec by id.
- **`spec_list`** — List specs with optional status filter.
- **`spec_set_status`** — Update satisfaction state (unknown/satisfied/violated/waived) with optional evidence note.
- **`spec_link_task`** — Associate a spec with a planner task.
- **`spec_unlink_task`** — Remove spec↔task association.
- **`spec_summary`** — Roll up spec counts/status for dashboards or cron hints.

## `verify` — `/mcp/verify`

- **`verify_run`** — Run a recorded HTTP check (or shell if host enables shell verification).
- **`verify_run_spec`** — Execute verification tied to a spec id.
- **`verify_get`** — Fetch one stored verify run by id.
- **`verify_list`** — List recent verify runs for the project.
- **`verify_compare`** — Diff stdout_text between two runs.

## `release` — `/mcp/release`

- **`release_trigger`** — Trigger release automation (webhook / EB) when host policy allows.
- **`release_get`** — Fetch one release job row by id.
- **`release_list`** — List recent release jobs.

## `probe` — `/mcp/probe`

- **`probe_http`** — Stateless GET/POST to a URL with timeout and body snippet (no persistent run record).
- **`probe_http_assert`** — Same as probe_http plus expected status / body substring assertion.

## `loop` — `/mcp/loop`

- **`loop_open`** — Start an iteration-budget loop tied optionally to a ledger run.
- **`loop_get`** — Read loop state by id.
- **`loop_step`** — Increment iteration counter for an open loop (end-of-tick bookkeeping).
- **`loop_close`** — Close a loop when work completes or is cancelled.
- **`loop_blocker_add`** — Record why the loop cannot advance (human input, failing verify, etc.).
- **`loop_blocker_clear`** — Clear blockers when resolved.
- **`loop_list_open`** — List open loops for the project (recent first).

## `diff` — `/mcp/diff`

- **`diff_baseline_set`** — Store a named JSON baseline for later regression compare.
- **`diff_baseline_get`** — Fetch one baseline by name.
- **`diff_baseline_list`** — List baselines for the project.
- **`diff_compare`** — Compare current JSON object to a stored baseline.

## `evidence` — `/mcp/evidence`

- **`evidence_attach`** — Attach proof (logs, outputs) to a spec/deploy/verify context.
- **`evidence_list`** — List evidence rows with optional linkage filters.
- **`evidence_bundle_export`** — Export a markdown bundle of evidence for handoff.

## `approval` — `/mcp/approval`

- **`approval_request`** — Human gate before a risky action; creates a pending approval.
- **`approval_resolve`** — Approve or reject a pending approval id.
- **`approval_get`** — Fetch one approval row.
- **`approval_list_pending`** — List approvals awaiting human action.

## `cron` — `/mcp/cron`

- **`cron_tick_snapshot`** — Start of a scheduled agent tick: one JSON bundle of planner ready tasks, loops/blockers, approvals, spec rollup, ledger open runs, optional queue depth.
- **`cron_iteration_checkpoint`** — End of tick: optionally `loop_step` then ledger append in one call.

## `memory` — `/mcp/memory`

- **`memory_ref_put`** — Store a short `ref_key` pointing at scratch, artifact, task, spec, ledger_run, or handoff for post-flush reload.
- **`memory_ref_list`** — List refs for the project (recent first).
- **`memory_ref_resolve`** — Expand a ref to summary + target payload.
- **`memory_ref_delete`** — Remove a ref key when obsolete.

## `focus` — `/mcp/focus`

- **`focus_add`** — Pin scratch rows into the working set to reload after context flush.
- **`focus_remove`** — Drop a scratch id from the focus set.
- **`focus_list`** — List scratch ids currently in focus.
- **`focus_export`** — Export focus rows for session bundles.

## `session` — `/mcp/session`

- **`session_restore`** — After a context flush: one JSON bundle (handoff excerpt, focus, memory refs, planner snapshot, etc.).
- **`session_sanity_check`** — Validate workspace invariants after restore (orphan refs, broken focus, etc.).
